826
00:53:16,190 --> 00:53:17,917
[BEA]
Of course.

827
00:53:18,357 --> 00:53:23,380
<i>♪</i>

828
00:53:27,556 --> 00:53:29,920
God bless you, sir.
God bless you, ma'am.

829
00:53:44,423 --> 00:53:45,753
[WORKER]
These are ready to go.

830
00:53:47,390 --> 00:53:48,623
[WORKER]
Give us a hand.

831
00:53:48,623 --> 00:53:51,214
♪
[typing]

832
00:53:57,390 --> 00:53:59,956
[BEA] Whatever will
they think of next?

833
00:53:59,956 --> 00:54:01,888
[SECRETARY]
May I help you?

834
00:54:04,189 --> 00:54:06,454
Um, we're here to
see Thomas Haddington.

835
00:54:06,455 --> 00:54:08,012
And you are?

836
00:54:09,023 --> 00:54:11,682
We're his parents.

837
00:54:12,188 --> 00:54:13,421
We have a gift for our son.

838
00:54:13,422 --> 00:54:14,789
[SECRETARY]
Mr. Haddington': away.

839
00:54:14,789 --> 00:54:17,277
But I'd be happy to
receive it on his behalf.

840
00:54:17,422 --> 00:54:19,684
[EDWARD] Perhaps we
could leave it for him.

841
00:54:30,188 --> 00:54:33,415
[EDWARD]You watch,
Bea, he'll come home.

