01:00:08,945 --> 01:00:11,910
I'm sorry, but I can't give your
father what he's asking for.

896
01:00:11,910 --> 01:00:12,844
All he wants is--

897
01:00:12,845 --> 01:00:14,511
I know what he wants.

898
01:00:14,511 --> 01:00:15,910
[EMILY]
Then give it to him.

899
01:00:15,910 --> 01:00:18,210
You're a minister;
he's a dying man.

900
01:00:18,211 --> 01:00:19,944
You can't give him
a simple prayer?

901
01:00:19,944 --> 01:00:22,342
Look, if it's so simple,
then why don't you do it?

902
01:00:26,344 --> 01:00:28,866
I don't believe in miracles.

903
01:01:27,708 --> 01:01:32,708
The fourth candle of Advent,
our last before Christmas Eve,

904
01:01:32,708 --> 01:01:37,936
represents the peace of God,
who passes all understanding.

905
01:01:38,274 --> 01:01:41,173
In the coming days of Christmas,

906
01:01:41,174 --> 01:01:44,207
let us be instruments
of this peace,

907
01:01:44,208 --> 01:01:46,875
Shining light where
there is darkness,

908
01:01:46,875 --> 01:01:50,040
hope where there is despair,

909
01:01:50,041 --> 01:01:54,030
sowing joy where
there is sadness...

910
01:01:58,375 --> 01:02:01,239
...and faith where
there is doubt.

911
01:02:17,173 --> 01:02:19,573
You asked me
to fill your pulpit,

912
01:02:19,574 --> 01:02:22,040
and instead
I emptied your church.

913
01:02:22,040 --> 01:02:24,666
You mustn't take all the credit.

914
01:02:25,007 --> 01:02:27,235
I did ask you to come.

915
01:02:28,574 --> 01:02:31,563
I am a man of faith,
Lady Camdon.

916
01:02:32,007 --> 01:02:34,939
I believe God worked
in the appointed time.

917
01:02:35,673 --> 01:02:39,873
But in our modern age,
the lame don't walk,

918
01:02:39,873 --> 01:02:44,205
blind men do not see,
and the sick die.

919
01:02:44,206 --> 01:02:46,729
But sometimes they live.

920
01:02:48,606 --> 01:02:50,765
Walk with me, Reverend.

921
01:02:54,072 --> 01:02:55,871
