But when he lit
the candle to pray...

926
01:03:06,538 --> 01:03:09,663
...well, he nearly burned
the vestry to the ground.

927
01:03:10,072 --> 01:03:12,671
The poor dear was in despair,

928
01:03:12,672 --> 01:03:16,005
and then, within
the church walls,

929
01:03:16,006 --> 01:03:18,171
a treasure was discovered,

930
01:03:18,171 --> 01:03:21,399
several gold crosses
and a ruby brooch.

931
01:03:22,105 --> 01:03:23,696
A hidden treasure?

932
01:03:23,872 --> 01:03:26,571
Well, had it not
been for the fire,

933
01:03:26,572 --> 01:03:28,505
it would've remained hidden.

934
01:03:28,505 --> 01:03:31,238
And thankfully, there was just
enough to repair the church

935
01:03:31,238 --> 01:03:33,004
And to provide for Gladbury's

936
01:03:33,005 --> 01:03:35,596
impoverished
families that winter.

937
01:03:37,171 --> 01:03:39,570
The very first
Christmas Candle

938
01:03:39,571 --> 01:03:42,765
went to my
great-great-great-grandmother.

939
01:03:44,171 --> 01:03:49,069
Once she was a
hopeless orphan, and then...

940
01:03:55,537 --> 01:03:58,770
Miracles are part of
our inheritance, Reverend.

941
01:03:58,771 --> 01:04:00,827
Tell that to Mrs. Hopewell.

942
01:04:01,270 --> 01:04:04,403
I believe you'll find
Mrs. Hopewell': faith to be much

943
01:04:04,404 --> 01:04:07,665
stronger than the grief
she's feeling now.

944
01:04:09,770 --> 01:04:12,770
Your doubts don't
trouble me, Reverend.

945
01:04:12,770 --> 01:04:17,702
On the contrary,
they inspire my faith.

946
01:04:46,003 --> 01:04:47,935
[honk]

947
01:05:06,901 --> 01:05:08,901
[BEA] Edward,
have a look at this!

948
01:05:08,901 --> 01:05:12,901
It's a carriage
that pulls itself!

949
01:05:12,901 --> 01:05:14,890
In all my days...

950
01:05:20,401 --> 01:05:23,492
Bea! It's Thomas!

951
01:05:24,002 --> 01:05:25,234
It's Thomas.

952
01:05:25,234 --> 01:05:27,200
[THOMAS]
Father. Mother.

953
01:05:31,067 --> 01:05:35,830
Oh, look at you,
handsome and fancy!

954
01:05:36,334 --> 01:05:37,767
That carriage of yours!

955
01:05:37,768 --> 01:05:41,100
It's called a Stanley Steamer,
