01:09:39,927 --> 01:09:42,593
Did I not say to you
that if you would believe,

1000
01:09:42,593 --> 01:09:44,426
You would see the glory of God.

1001
01:09:44,426 --> 01:09:45,592
And they took away
the stone from the

1002
01:09:45,593 --> 01:09:47,526
place where the
dead man was lying,

1003
01:09:47,526 --> 01:09:50,025
and Jesus lifted up
his eyes and said,

1004
01:09:50,026 --> 01:09:52,159
"Father, I thank you
that you have heard..."

1005
01:09:52,159 --> 01:09:54,192
And these are written
that you might believe

1006
01:09:54,193 --> 01:09:57,092
that Jesus is the
Christ, the son of God,

1007
01:09:57,093 --> 01:09:59,426
and that in believing,
you might have life.

1008
01:09:59,426 --> 01:10:01,858
Behold there came a leper
and worshipped him,

1009
01:10:01,859 --> 01:10:05,725
"Lord, if thou wilt, thou
canst make me clean."

1010
01:10:05,726 --> 01:10:07,026
And Jesus put forth his hand...

1011
01:10:07,026 --> 01:10:09,159
My little daughter is
at the point of death.

1012
01:10:09,159 --> 01:10:12,025
I pray thee, Lord,
come and lay hands on her,

1013
01:10:12,026 --> 01:10:13,692
that she might be healed.

1014
01:10:13,692 --> 01:10:17,556
If I may but touch his
garment, I shall be whole.

1015
01:10:17,759 --> 01:10:20,258
If thou canst believe, all
things are possible to him...

1016
01:10:20,258 --> 01:10:22,157
The father of
the child cried out,

1017
01:10:22,158 --> 01:10:26,857
"Lord, I believe,
help my unbelief!"

1018
01:10:26,858 --> 01:10:31,091
And he said to her,
"Damsel, arise."

1019
01:10:31,092 --> 01:10:34,158
And they were astonished,
a great astonishment.

1020
01:10:34,158 --> 01:10:37,920
Speak the word,
and my servant shall be here.

1021
01:10:38,425 --> 01:10:40,091
<i>♪</i>

1022
01:10:40,092 --> 01:10:45,888
And Jesus said unto them,
"Thy faith has made you whole."

1023
01:10:48,858 --> 01:10:52,847
<i>♪</i>

1024
01:11:11,191 --> 01:11:14,248
David. David.

1025
01:11:17,991 --> 01:11:20,014
He's asleep.

1026
01:11:33,090 --> 01:11:36,523
[DAVID] My wife and daughter
died of consumption.

1027
01:11:41,256 --> 01:11:46,483
I prayed. I even
believed for a miracle.

1028
01:11:53,356 --> 01:11:55,515
[DAVID]
But God did nothing.

1029
01:11:58,055 --> 01:11:59,749
Oh, David.

1030
01:12:02,922 --> 01:12:08,150
[DAVID] One day my faith was so
certain, and then it was gone.

1031
01:12:10,356 --> 01:12:13,583
There was a time
when I could not...

1032
01:12:14,922 --> 01:12:19,752
...utter a prayer or step
foot in a church.

1033
01:12:23,855 --> 01:12:27,412
I believe I've made
my peace with God.

1034
01:12:30,088 --> 01:12:33,054
But still I was a
different man before.

1035
01:12:34,921 --> 01:12:40,548
The love I shared,
the hope I had...

1036
01:12:44,421 --> 01:12:47,410
Some things,
they cannot be restored.

1037
01:12:49,188 --> 01:12:51,415
I do hope you're wrong.

1038
01:12:55,487 --> 01:12:58,510
Such a hope is too great a risk.

1039
01:12:59,520 --> 01:13:03,077
But I wonder what you
risk living without it.

1040
01:13:18,886 --> 01:13:20,511
[DAVID] [weakly]
I should go.

1041
01:13:33,186 --> 01:13:39,050
[Emily sobs]

1042
01:14:43,150 --> 01:14:44,216
Bea.

1043
01:14:44,217 --> 01:14:47,550
He won't light it.
I'll light it for him.

1044
01:14:47,551 --> 01:14:49,141
It's of no use.

1045
01:14:49,250 --> 01:14:51,649
Anyway, we don't even
know if it's the right one.

1046
01:14:51,650 --> 01:14:53,550
Well then we'll find out.

1047
01:14:53,551 --> 01:14:55,850
We did everything we knew to do.

1048
01:14:55,850 --> 01:14:59,475
We gave away every last candle,
and this one came back.

1049
01:15:00,750 --> 01:15:02,306
Twice.

1050
01:15:06,650 --> 01:15:10,082
This could be
our miracle, Edward.

1051
01:15:19,316 --> 01:15:21,715
I hope I'm not overstepping
my boundaries,

1052
01:15:21,716 --> 01:15:25,479
but I know just the person to
give the candle to this year.

1053
01:15:26,083 --> 01:15:28,208
David Richmond.

1054
01:15:29,515 --> 01:15:31,708
Think of it, Edward.

1055
01:15:31,849 --> 01:15:35,149
Your father gave the candle
to Reverend Pillington.

1056
01:15:35,149 --> 01:15:38,048
And as we know, David is a far
greater wretch than he ever was.

1057
01:15:38,049 --> 01:15:40,381
[BEA] You make a compelling
argument, but I don't--

1058
01:15:40,382 --> 01:15:42,814
Don't tell me you've
given the candle away.

1059
01:15:46,015 --> 01:15:50,038
This is the candle,
isn't it'! Splendid.

1060
01:15:50,215 --> 01:15:52,215
Then we're in agreement?

1061
01:15:52,215 --> 01:15:53,348
[BEA] Lady Camdon,
I don't think--

1062
01:15:53,349 --> 01:15:59,315
[EDWARD]Yes, we'll give
the candle to David.

1063
01:15:59,315 --> 01:16:00,678
Good.

1064
01:16:02,681 --> 01:16:06,408
[LADY CAMDON] Lord knows,
he could use a little light.

1065
01:16:09,748 --> 01:16:13,078
But he doesn't
even believe in the candle.

1066
01:16:18,514 --> 01:16:19,537
Edward.

1067
01:16:24,981 --> 01:16:27,243
Edward, please!

1068
01:16:35,580 --> 01:16:36,880
Mr. Haddington.

1069
01:16:36,880 --> 01:16:38,903
May I have a word'!

1070
01:16:46,480 --> 01:16:48,309
The Christmas Candle.

1071
01:16:49,413 --> 01:16:51,813
You're giving the candle to me?

1072
01:16:51,814 --> 01:16:55,802
[EDWARD]Well, you
weren't the first choice.

1073
01:17:01,679 --> 01:17:03,509
What am I to do with it.

1074
01:17:03,679 --> 01:17:07,668
Just light it and...
just light it.

1075
01:17:08,913 --> 01:17:13,368
Just do something
good for Gladbury.

1076
01:17:40,578 --> 01:17:42,306
[DAVID]
Emily.

1077
01:17:51,311 --> 01:17:52,834
[DAVID]
In church.

1078
01:17:53,144 --> 01:17:55,235
And on your own accord.

1079
01:17:55,411 --> 01:17:57,172
It's true.

1080
01:17:58,378 --> 01:18:01,344
Am I to think that
you've come to believe?

1081
01:18:01,712 --> 01:18:03,507
I don't know.

1082
01:18:04,044 --> 01:18:05,839
I want to.

1083
01:18:06,144 --> 01:18:09,210
In times like this,
it would be comforting.

1084
01:18:09,211 --> 01:18:11,336
Don't think less of me.

1085
01:18:13,677 --> 01:18:15,404
I have a problem.

1086
01:18:17,344 --> 01:18:20,177
Cousin Charlie was given
this blasted Christmas Candle,

1087
01:18:20,177 --> 01:18:24,701
and the poor boy
has given it to me.

1088
01:18:26,077 --> 01:18:28,477
Who could refuse
a gift like that?

1089
01:18:28,477 --> 01:18:30,477
Now all I can do is pray.

1090
01:18:30,477 --> 01:18:33,909
I feel as though
I owe it to him.

1091
01:18:38,077 --> 01:18:40,009
That is a problem.

1092
01:18:40,977 --> 01:18:41,810
[banging on door]

1093
01:18:41,810 --> 01:18:43,742
[EDWARD]
Yes, yes, I'm coming.

1094
01:18:47,043 --> 01:18:49,176
Reverend Richmond, Miss Barstow.

1095
01:18:49,177 --> 01:18:51,043
[DAVID]
Mr. Haddington, a word.

1096
01:18:51,043 --> 01:18:52,242
Reverend!

1097
01:18:52,242 --> 01:18:54,299
Miss Barstow!

1098
01:18:54,476 --> 01:18:55,576
Is there a problem?

1099
01:18:55,576 --> 01:18:58,475
[DAVID] On the contrary.
A great and wondrous miracle

1100
01:18:58,476 --> 01:19:00,567
has taken place this
Christmas season.

1101
01:19:01,309 --> 01:19:05,242
It seems that the angel
has blessed not one,

1102
01:19:05,242 --> 01:19:08,242
but two Christmas
Candles this year.

1103
01:19:08,242 --> 01:19:11,508
And now that I think of it,
how small is my faith,

1104
01:19:11,509 --> 01:19:14,242
to think that this angel
might stop at two.

1105
01:19:14,242 --> 01:19:16,174
Why not three or four?

1106
01:19:16,343 --> 01:19:18,209
Or maybe there are no
limits to the blessings

1107
01:19:18,209 --> 01:19:20,408
the Good Lord might
bestow upon Gladbury.

1108
01:19:20,408 --> 01:19:21,674
[BEA]
Well, we can explain.

1109
01:19:21,675 --> 01:19:23,008
Edward tripped, and then--

1110
01:19:23,009 --> 01:19:24,009
you came around.

1111
01:19:24,009 --> 01:19:24,908
There was an accident.

1112
01:19:24,909 --> 01:19:26,541
Yes, we'd lost the candle.

1113
01:19:26,542 --> 01:19:28,074
So I said, "Why don't we
give all the candles?"

1114
01:19:28,075 --> 01:19:28,909
Bea.

1115
01:19:28,909 --> 01:19:29,708
And Edward said--

1116
01:19:29,709 --> 01:19:30,975
We meant no harm.

1117
01:19:30,976 --> 01:19:32,669
But you've given us false hope.

1118
01:19:32,875 --> 01:19:35,136
Surely you can see that.

1119
01:19:39,642 --> 01:19:41,369
How could you?

1120
01:19:41,874 --> 01:19:44,874
How could you question my
intentions for the people of

1121
01:19:44,874 --> 01:19:48,307
Gladbury when you, yourselves
so blatantly misled them?

1122
01:19:48,308 --> 01:19:50,674
I fear this Christmas will end
in nothing but disappointment,

1123
01:19:50,674 --> 01:19:52,807
And you and your fairy
tales are to blame.

1124
01:19:52,808 --> 01:19:54,001
[Bea gasps]

1125
01:19:56,708 --> 01:19:59,970
Perhaps it was providence
that kept me in Gladbury.

1126
01:20:02,307 --> 01:20:07,873
<i>♪</i>

1127
01:20:07,873 --> 01:20:09,873
Well, here we are again.

1128
01:20:09,873 --> 01:20:11,964
[DAVID]
Thank you, Mrs. Hopewell.

1129
01:20:12,140 --> 01:20:14,163
I can never repay you.

1130
01:20:23,974 --> 01:20:27,202
I know what it is
to suffer a great loss.

1131
01:20:33,306 --> 01:20:35,169
Allow me, Reverend.

1132
01:20:51,739 --> 01:20:53,399
It's time.

1133
01:20:56,706 --> 01:21:02,006
On Christmas Eve, we light
the final candle of Advent,

1134
01:21:02,006 --> 01:21:07,739
the Christ Candle, for only
in Christ do we find the hope,

1135
01:21:07,739 --> 01:21:13,638
love, joy, and peace that we
have come to know this season.

1136
01:21:15,238 --> 01:21:18,670
Christmas Eve
holds a special place

1137
01:21:18,671 --> 01:21:21,671
in the heart of every believer,

1138
01:21:21,671 --> 01:21:26,831
and nowhere is this more true
than in the town of Gladbury.

1139
01:21:28,471 --> 01:21:34,204
Many of you have no
doubt come to rejoice

1140
01:21:34,204 --> 01:21:36,830
in the miracle of the
Christmas Candle.

1141
01:21:38,204 --> 01:21:41,704
But regretfully,
tonight you shall see this

1142
01:21:41,705 --> 01:21:45,864
long-standing tradition
come to an end.

1143
01:21:46,071 --> 01:21:49,162
[gasps]

1144
01:22:09,503 --> 01:22:11,492
Father?

1145
01:22:14,236 --> 01:22:16,836
I would now like to ask
the recipient of the

1146
01:22:16,836 --> 01:22:21,030
Christmas Candle
to please stand.

1147
01:22:24,070 --> 01:22:27,298
[murmurs]

1148
01:22:28,970 --> 01:22:30,636
[DAVID] Now more than
ever I see the urgent need

1149
01:22:30,636 --> 01:22:33,136
to speak on the virtue
of enduring faith,

1150
01:22:33,136 --> 01:22:34,169
a faith that endures

1151
01:22:34,170 --> 01:22:36,869
disappointment, and
unanswered prayer.

1152
01:22:36,869 --> 01:22:40,368
A faith that relies not on
the hollow promises of men,

1153
01:22:40,369 --> 01:22:43,062
but on the sovereignty
of Almighty God.

1154
01:22:44,336 --> 01:22:45,700
<i>I...</i>

1155
01:22:48,536 --> 01:22:49,797
<i>I...</i>

1156
01:22:49,969 --> 01:22:51,569
I've got something to say!

1157
01:22:51,569 --> 01:22:53,830
[gasps and chatter]

1158
01:23:02,568 --> 01:23:04,035
I can speak!

1159
01:23:04,035 --> 01:23:05,868
[joyful voices]

1160
01:23:05,868 --> 01:23:08,467
I prayed. Every day I prayed,

1161
01:23:08,468 --> 01:23:11,668
And then I woke up this
morning, and I could talk.

1162
01:23:11,668 --> 01:23:14,725
I don't understand it.
I even gave my candle away.

1163
01:23:15,635 --> 01:23:18,067
But my favorite scripture says,

1164
01:23:18,068 --> 01:23:20,835
"With God,
all things are possible."

1165
01:23:20,835 --> 01:23:25,062
Now I'm never going to stop
talking, especially about this!

1166
01:23:25,335 --> 01:23:27,892
[applause]

1167
01:23:30,468 --> 01:23:32,334
I don't know how this happened,

1168
01:23:32,335 --> 01:23:35,734
but my wife also received
the Christmas Candle.

1169
01:23:35,734 --> 01:23:37,067
For my husband.

1170
01:23:37,068 --> 01:23:40,397
As many of you know,
I was stuck on the bottle.

1171
01:23:40,667 --> 01:23:43,000
Like never before, I prayed.

1172
01:23:43,001 --> 01:23:45,700
And I found I was
drinking less and less.

1173
01:23:45,701 --> 01:23:47,792
Which really is a miracle.

1174
01:23:48,400 --> 01:23:51,700
[applause]

1175
01:23:51,701 --> 01:23:53,500
I was hopeless.

1176
01:23:53,500 --> 01:23:56,489
I'd lost everything.

1177
01:23:56,967 --> 01:24:00,365
And now, nothing': lost at all.

1178
01:24:00,633 --> 01:24:03,532
It's all been found.

1179
01:24:03,533 --> 01:24:05,658
[applause]

1180
01:24:06,566 --> 01:24:09,133
[MR. FINCH] I've been out
of a job for some time now,

1181
01:24:09,133 --> 01:24:11,732
and found myself
in debt up to my ears.

1182
01:24:11,733 --> 01:24:13,166
But then, our landlady--

1183
01:24:13,167 --> 01:24:15,466
[MRS. FINCH] She forgave
us our debts in full.

1184
01:24:15,466 --> 01:24:17,199
[MR. FINCH] And if
that wasn't enough,

1185
01:24:17,199 --> 01:24:19,399
well I found work
at the Leonard house.

1186
01:24:19,399 --> 01:24:22,332
It makes a man feel good to
provide for his family again.

1187
01:24:22,333 --> 01:24:26,166
And my wife, she's found
a good friend in Ms. Leonard.

1188
01:24:26,166 --> 01:24:27,399
[MRS. FINCH]
Yes, this dear woman,

1189
01:24:27,399 --> 01:24:29,232
she's taught our kids to knit.

1190
01:24:29,232 --> 01:24:30,965
[laughs and applause]

1191
01:24:30,966 --> 01:24:32,399
[JOE] [on verge of tears]
My name's Joe.

1192
01:24:32,399 --> 01:24:34,065
I'm not really a religious man.

1193
01:24:34,066 --> 01:24:38,828
I asked for the candle,
and it's saved my cat.

1194
01:24:39,532 --> 01:24:43,226
It may not seem much, but
she means a great deal to me.

1195
01:24:43,865 --> 01:24:46,331
I never thought I'd get
the Christmas Candle,

1196
01:24:46,332 --> 01:24:47,732
but thank God I did.

1197
01:24:47,732 --> 01:24:50,298
[applause]

1198
01:24:50,298 --> 01:24:54,064
[PHINEAS]The candle was
for me old man, Oliver Barber.

1199
01:24:54,065 --> 01:24:54,964
[DELILAH]
He was blind.

1200
01:24:54,965 --> 01:24:58,954
As you may have heard,
dad died this morning.

1201
01:24:59,699 --> 01:25:02,365
[DELILAH] And just before
he left us, he whispered,

1202
01:25:02,365 --> 01:25:03,631
"I can see."

1203
01:25:03,632 --> 01:25:08,198
"I can see." His prayer was
answered,just as he'd hoped.

1204
01:25:08,198 --> 01:25:10,720
He saw Jesus.

1205
01:25:15,831 --> 01:25:17,997
When I received the candle,

1206
01:25:17,998 --> 01:25:20,731
I thought my prayer'd
be answered one way,

1207
01:25:20,731 --> 01:25:23,330
so I took a step of faith.

1208
01:25:23,331 --> 01:25:26,320
Only it was in
the wrong direction.

1209
01:25:26,531 --> 01:25:29,797
But then I stumbled into
the arms of Hardy Collins,

1210
01:25:29,798 --> 01:25:32,130
the man of my dreams,

1211
01:25:32,130 --> 01:25:34,963
and just this morning,
he asked me to be his wife.

1212
01:25:34,964 --> 01:25:36,331
[excited gasps]

1213
01:25:36,331 --> 01:25:39,297
My answer's yes!

1214
01:25:40,964 --> 01:25:43,830
[EMILY]
I don't know what to say,

1215
01:25:43,830 --> 01:25:50,228
except I prayed for
my father, and here he is.

1216
01:25:53,463 --> 01:25:56,729
[WOMAN] I hadn't spoke
to my sister in ten years.

1217
01:25:56,730 --> 01:25:59,830
I even stopped coming
to church because of her.

1218
01:25:59,830 --> 01:26:01,529
But we both
received the candle...

1219
01:26:01,530 --> 01:26:06,729
So Reverend, have you changed
your mind about Gladbury?

1220
01:26:06,729 --> 01:26:10,127
I'm afraid this has only
confirmed my suspicions.

1221
01:26:10,363 --> 01:26:12,658
How can you not believe?

1222
01:26:13,196 --> 01:26:18,562
I believe...
but I do not belong.

1223
01:26:18,562 --> 01:26:20,062
[thunder]

1224
01:26:20,063 --> 01:26:22,392
[applause]

1225
01:26:27,462 --> 01:26:29,223
Quite a night.

1226
01:26:30,028 --> 01:26:32,460
More than I could have imagined.

1227
01:26:34,629 --> 01:26:37,186
I know he'll come back, Edward.

1228
01:26:37,828 --> 01:26:43,455
Not tonight. Maybe not until
after we've both gone,

1229
01:26:44,329 --> 01:26:46,395
but I don't have
to see it to believe

1230
01:26:46,395 --> 01:26:49,554
that our son will
come home again.

1231
01:26:52,995 --> 01:26:54,984
[thunder]

1232
01:26:55,628 --> 01:26:58,389
[DAVID] God help
me in my unbelief.

1233
01:27:09,794 --> 01:27:13,192
[thunder and wind]

1234
01:27:25,994 --> 01:27:30,693
[ELEANOR] There are
miracles all around, ♪

1235
01:27:30,694 --> 01:27:34,393
♪ Miracles yet to be found. ♪

1236
01:27:34,393 --> 01:27:40,359
♪ Hid in every heart is
an answered prayer. ♪

1237
01:27:40,360 --> 01:27:42,693
[DAVID JOINS]
♪ Like a candle': flame, ♪

1238
01:27:42,694 --> 01:27:46,648
♪ Hope will lead us there. ♪

1239
01:27:47,126 --> 01:27:49,992
[DAVID]
♪ When the darkness comes, ♪

1240
01:27:49,993 --> 01:27:52,859
♪ Let the light shine through, ♪

1241
01:27:52,859 --> 01:27:58,558
♪ A spark of faith
will ignite in you. ♪

1242
01:27:58,559 --> 01:28:03,692
♪ In a candle': glow,
a Virgin's womb, ♪

1243
01:28:03,693 --> 01:28:10,319
♪ In a simple prayer
in the empty tomb. ♪

1244
01:28:11,192 --> 01:28:16,659
[BOTH] There are
